issue.title: Implement pytest as test suite run in the CI
issue.body:
### Problem

There are no tests - yet - neither a CI system running them in different platforms and python versions.

### Proposed solution

Implement  a CI system that uses `pytest` to run tests once they are in place. `Sunglass` uses `poetry` as the package manager, therefore something similar to what is done in the [StrainMap project](https://github.com/ImperialCollegeLondon/strainmap/blob/fe08324240832285332b03ca86dc3778337bf627/.github/workflows/ci.yml#L16) should work. 

Good first issue... to get familiar with testing in a CI system.

issue.title: Implement pytest as test suite run in the CI
issue.body:
### Problem

There are no tests - yet - neither a CI system running them in different platforms and python versions.

### Proposed solution

Implement  a CI system that uses `pytest` to run tests once they are in place. `Sunglass` uses `poetry` as the package manager, therefore something similar to what is done in the [StrainMap project](https://github.com/ImperialCollegeLondon/strainmap/blob/fe08324240832285332b03ca86dc3778337bf627/.github/workflows/ci.yml#L16) should work. 

Good first issue... to get familiar with testing in a CI system.
